1
00:01:33,580 --> 00:01:35,980
=Filter=

2
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:38,940
=Episode 29=

3
00:01:47,230 --> 00:01:48,680
Hurry, hurry.

4
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,510
Who's here?

5
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:01,000
Uncle, let's go to the hospital
for a check-up.

6
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,000
He said he was too big

7
00:02:05,590 --> 00:02:06,560
for us to move him.

8
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,190
He insisted on waiting for Chengcheng.

9
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:10,910
I brought my boyfriend to help.

10
00:02:17,410 --> 00:02:19,750
Uncle, let's go to the hospital first.

11
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,430
You're Gu Yu, right?

12
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,150
Where is Chengcheng?

13
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:29,560
I've fallen,

14
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,960
and she's not even here to check on me.

15
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:33,960
Chengcheng, she...

16
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:37,190
Chengcheng is on her way back.

17
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:41,590
You're Chengcheng's boss, right?

18
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,000
Tell me.

19
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,960
Where exactly is Su Chengcheng?

20
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,560
Where was Dad hurt?

21
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:54,680
Why are you standing here?

22
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,150
Why haven't you gone to the hospital?

23
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:58,150
Why are you the only one who came back?

24
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,840
Didn't Chengcheng contact you?

25
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,910
Uncle insisted on waiting
for Chengcheng.

26
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,680
I called an ambulance.

27
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,080
No need.

28
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,310
Let's wait for Chengcheng.

29
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:11,000
Don't call.

30
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:13,870
Your dad's fine.

31
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:17,190
He's just upset
that Chengcheng lied to us.

32
00:03:17,710 --> 00:03:18,750
Your dad wants to see her.

33
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,120
Su Chengcheng, Tang Qi,

34
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,400
and you, Lin Yuan,

35
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:29,000
including Gu Yu.

36
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,030
You all told me

37
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,390
that Chengcheng was on a business trip.

38
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,080
But two hours ago,

39
00:03:35,180 --> 00:03:36,510
Chengcheng's colleague came here

40
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:38,430
and said she hadn't been
on any business trip.

41
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:39,470
She just took sick leave.

42
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:44,360
You were all just fooling me.

43
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,630
She's not at home

44
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,560
and not at work.

45
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,080
Where has she gone?

46
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,800
Come out.

47
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:08,870
Uncle, Aunt.

48
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,180
As soon as Chengcheng got the news,

49
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,760
she told me to come here at once.

50
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:19,720
What's with you?

51
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,870
Why are you dressed like this?

52
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,070
Take off that outfit.

53
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:25,950
I won't scold you.

54
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,430
Dad, Mom.

55
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,190
There's something

56
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,240
I need to tell you.

57
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,390
Chengcheng got

58
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:07,310
a filter that can change her appearance,

59
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:12,190
but it's made her invisible now?

60
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,510
Chengcheng is inside this doll,

61
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,750
but without her outer clothes,

62
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,390
we can't see her?

63
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,150
Yes.

64
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:29,510
Whatever she looks like,

65
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:31,050
she's still my daughter.

66
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,270
It's okay, Chengcheng.

67
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,120
Let me see you.

68
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,040
Chengcheng...

69
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,110
Chengcheng.

70
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,150
Mom.

71
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,800
- Dad.
- Chengcheng.

72
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,240
Don't be afraid.

73
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,480
We'll find a way.

74
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,240
There must be a way to solve it.

75
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,750
Dad, Mom.

76
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,800
The filter blocked Chengcheng's voice.

77
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,720
She can only communicate

78
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,000
by WeChat or by writing.

79
00:06:56,630 --> 00:06:58,000
If you keep holding her like this,

80
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:02,950
she won't be able to say anything.

81
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,400
Sit down first.

82
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,560
Chengcheng.

83
00:07:46,950 --> 00:07:48,750
Tell us whatever you want to say.

84
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,680
You can write it down.

85
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:05,040
Dad, Mom.

86
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:06,760
I'm sorry.

87
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,310
I've made you worry.

88
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,350
It's okay.

89
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,750
Don't be afraid.

90
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:25,680
How could this happen?

91
00:08:41,510 --> 00:08:44,510
I've been reflecting on this these days.

92
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,120
The filter has always been unstable,

93
00:08:47,910 --> 00:08:49,600
but why do I only

94
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,270
want to take off the filter today

95
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,000
when no one can see me?

96
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,320
When everyone

97
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,960
could still see me,

98
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,270
why didn't I make up my mind
to take it off?

99
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:06,360
Even though I knew it wasn't right,

100
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,910
why did I keep using the filter

101
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:11,120
and letting it upgrade each time?

102
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,600
Everything with you is wrong.

103
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,280
What more do we need to ask you?

104
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,150
Don't delay our next interview.

105
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,240
Su Chengcheng,

106
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,840
we know the result now.

107
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,080
You can go home now.

108
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,280
Ladies first.

109
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:26,510
Thank you.

110
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:33,200
I pretended not to care,

111
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,080
but in reality,

112
00:09:35,630 --> 00:09:37,870
I've always been dissatisfied
with my appearance.

113
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,910
I wanted to look
like other pretty girls,

114
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,270
not be ignored by anyone,

115
00:09:45,030 --> 00:09:47,550
and gain the affection and respect
of people my age.

116
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,670
Because of my anxiety
about my appearance,

117
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,750
I could never give up the filter,

118
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,390
which led to today's outcome.

119
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,870
The filter kept upgrading,

120
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,720
slowly devouring my true self.

121
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:08,000
Now, no one can see me.

122
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,870
It's us who have failed you.

123
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:21,390
Though we've always said
we didn't care about your looks,

124
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:26,150
we've always thought

125
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:28,120
you didn't look as good as your sister,

126
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,220
and it'd be hard for you to get married.

127
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,750
But we didn't mean any harm.

128
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,790
It was all for your good.

129
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:41,200
But we didn't expect this good intention

130
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,320
to put a lot of pressure on you.

131
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,560
Qingli,

132
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:49,200
introduce a boyfriend to Chengcheng.

133
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,910
Your sister hasn't even had a crush

134
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:54,120
since she was little.

135
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:19,550
I know you worry about me
because you love me.

136
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:22,840
I've never blamed you.

137
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:25,150
Did the interviewer criticize

138
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:26,670
the photo I edited for you?

139
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:28,870
Isn't this outfit too eye-catching?

140
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,240
Do you think others won't dress up?

141
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,440
Everyone will dress up

142
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,080
to save face, spending all they have.

143
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:37,200
Are these skirt pants too short?

144
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,790
This is called healthy.

145
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,320
Looking like a stick isn't beautiful.

146
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,390
That's sickly.

147
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:44,510
Chengcheng,

148
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:47,390
I've always comforted you
not to care about appearance

149
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,150
and sometimes purposely
looked unattractive

150
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:52,200
to show that I'm in this with you.

151
00:11:52,870 --> 00:11:55,630
But if I didn't think
appearance mattered,

152
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,600
why would I do such things?

153
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:01,550
I'm also one of those
who created appearance anxiety for you.

154
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:03,080
Sorry.

155
00:12:13,490 --> 00:12:14,360
During interviews,

156
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:17,270
I have judged people
based on their looks.

157
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,350
Sorry.

158
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:21,720
Beauty products sell beauty.

159
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:23,420
I hope the Marketing Department staff

160
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:24,500
can not only work hard

161
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,140
but also have a good appearance,

162
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,540
so they can be persuasive
when meeting clients.

163
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:34,820
I'll return to the palace.

164
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:37,660
Goodbye, Your Highness.

165
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,820
As my sister,

166
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:41,800
you've carried a lot of pressure

167
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:45,660
regarding appearance
since you were little.

168
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:49,700
Don't just dress up your doll
and do makeup for it.

169
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:52,300
You should put on makeup
and dress up too.

170
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:53,420
Look at you,

171
00:12:53,580 --> 00:12:55,260
not even bothering to tidy yourself up.

172
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:56,820
Your face is oily enough to fry food.

173
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:59,100
Since you're at home unemployed,

174
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,220
you should study how to dress up.

175
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:02,460
Dress yourself up.

176
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:05,340
It's fine if you can't find a man,

177
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:07,340
but it's deadly if you can't find a job.

178
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:10,060
Being pretty isn't my fault,

179
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:13,900
so I don't want to say sorry.

180
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,340
But...

181
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:28,180
Sorry.

182
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:47,620
Don't be upset or feel guilty.

183
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:51,740
It's me who wasn't confident
or brave enough.

184
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:54,820
Now, I understand

185
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:57,140
I can change how others see me.

186
00:13:57,940 --> 00:13:59,540
I really like the person I am now.

187
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:32,820
Chengcheng.

188
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,420
Mom.

189
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:37,060
Chengcheng.

190
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:41,900
Dad.

191
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:48,460
Uncle, Aunt.

192
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:51,140
Chengcheng is not alone this time.

193
00:14:51,820 --> 00:14:52,760
We're in this together.

194
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:55,460
We'll definitely find a way
to remove the filter.

195
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:14,660
(Don't lose your happiness
to unimportant people.)

196
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:30,700
Chengcheng,
let's sleep together tonight.

197
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:36,260
You must be hungry.

198
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,260
I made some late-night snacks for you.

199
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:45,620
It's here.

200
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,660
The gloves are for Chengcheng.

201
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,340
Thank you.

202
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,640
I'm thanking you on her behalf.

203
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:55,740
No.

204
00:15:55,820 --> 00:15:56,860
Chengcheng would say,

205
00:15:57,140 --> 00:15:58,900
"Thank you, my dear mom."

206
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:05,380
So childish.

207
00:16:05,380 --> 00:16:06,500
Alright, eat then.

208
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,260
If it's not enough, I'll make more.

209
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:09,620
It's enough.

210
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:10,900
They can't eat too much at night.

211
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:12,180
It's bad for digestion.

212
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,060
Right.

213
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,020
Eat then.

214
00:16:27,660 --> 00:16:29,860
Congrats on Su Chengcheng
for finding someone.

215
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:34,540
Thank you.

216
00:16:34,980 --> 00:16:35,940
With you all here,

217
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,620
even if I'm invisible forever,

218
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:39,140
I won't be afraid.

219
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:41,820
Can't you drink?

220
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,620
Chengcheng must be moved

221
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,060
to have such a good friend like me

222
00:16:51,060 --> 00:16:52,200
and such a beautiful sister

223
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:55,020
like you.

224
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:01,500
Tonight,

225
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,500
I'll sleep in my room.

226
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:17,860
Let's eat, everyone.

227
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:20,140
Time to eat.

228
00:17:21,530 --> 00:17:22,820
Wear the gloves to eat.

229
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:23,980
I don't want to.

230
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,180
(My Mom)

231
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:33,220
My mom is invisible.

232
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:35,220
No one can see her

233
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:36,820
or hear her.

234
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,340
Every time our family goes on a trip,

235
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:41,860
everyone can only see me and Dad,

236
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:43,340
but I know,

237
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:45,900
Mom has always been with us.

238
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,020
She loves me and Dad so much.

239
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:49,860
She often performs magic for me.

240
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:51,180
Tang Yuwen, you're lying.

241
00:17:51,180 --> 00:17:52,460
You don't have a mom.

242
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:55,500
Yeah, you're lying.
You don't have a mom.

243
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,060
- You're lying to us.
- I have a mom.

244
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:58,620
You don't have a mom.

245
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,820
- Tang Yuwen, you're lying.
- I do.

246
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:02,820
You don't have a mom.

247
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:03,820
You're lying.

248
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:05,180
You don't have a mom.

249
00:18:05,180 --> 00:18:07,460
I have a mom!

250
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:29,660
A bunch of stupid kids.

251
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,460
Tang Yuwen?

252
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,420
My son is a Tang?

253
00:18:40,580 --> 00:18:43,060
I married Tang Qi?

254
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,540
(Tang Qi)
If I'm trapped by this filter

255
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,060
and remain invisible,

256
00:18:58,900 --> 00:18:59,980
can you really accept

257
00:18:59,980 --> 00:19:01,620
an invisible girlfriend?

258
00:19:04,020 --> 00:19:06,300
Are you anxious
about your appearance again?

259
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,420
I'm talking about being invisible.

260
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:11,340
That's different

261
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:12,520
from thinking I'm not pretty.

262
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:34,300
I guess this is the benefit
of being invisible.

263
00:19:38,420 --> 00:19:39,260
Miss Su,

264
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:41,060
may I ask if you're free today?

265
00:19:43,620 --> 00:19:45,460
What could I possibly be busy with?

266
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:49,980
I'm free.

267
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,100
(Tang Qi)

268
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,180
Half an hour later,

269
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:53,460
I'll pick you up downstairs.

270
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,140
Let's have a date.

271
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,340
OK.

272
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:15,980
Keep walking.

273
00:20:25,860 --> 00:20:27,460
I had a dream last night.

274
00:20:27,780 --> 00:20:29,740
I dreamed our son was
in elementary school.

275
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:31,820
Do you know what our son's name is?

276
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:33,500
He's called Tang Yuwen (Chinese).

277
00:20:33,620 --> 00:20:35,500
Why isn't he called Tang Tiyu (Sports)?

278
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,460
What are you talking about?

279
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:39,420
How did you know I was speaking?

280
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:41,260
Your facial muscles were moving.

281
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,700
Come on, let's keep walking.

282
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:49,860
